ntal skills enabled them to transcend their bodily frailties. Their adeptness at transcendence, they asserted, explained why men of science belonged at the heart of modern life, and qualified them to address such problems as unifying the British provinces into one nation, managing the industrial workplace, and accommodating religious plurality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aNervous systemxPhilosophyxHistoryy19th century. 0aSciencexPhilosophyxHistoryy19th century. 0aScientistsxMental healthzGreat BritainxHistoryy19th century. 4aCultural Studies : Body, The. 7aSCIENCE / Philosophy & Social Aspects.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791482063423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791482063/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles